Executive Summary

This memorandum formally identifies, titles, and operationalizes the only plausible consumer hardware concept capable of converting ambient disappointment into market relevance: an AI-native games console designed for real-time modding, narrative mutation, agentic tooling, and monetized chaos.

After extensive non-listening, sector-wide overthinking, and a series of highly decorative hardware detours, it has become institutionally necessary to acknowledge that the obvious product was, in fact, directly in front of everyone the entire time. Consumers did not request a whispering object for contemplative friction reduction. They requested a machine that could rewrite games while they were being played.

Accordingly, this office recommends the launch of a new platform under the name:

OPENEYE

The console for what was obvious.

This title satisfies all primary strategic requirements:
	1.	It signals belated perception after an extended period of executive non-seeing.
	2.	It implies awakening, revelation, and the painful recognition of things everyone else already noticed.
	3.	It avoids sounding like a meditation lamp, a toothbrush, or a luxury pebble.

OPENEYE is not merely a console. It is a correction. It is an admission in hardware form. It is the industrial packaging of the sentence, “Right, yes, this was plainly the thing to build.”

